590
00:33:31.470 --> 00:33:34.970
with all your justproceedings in this cause.

591
00:33:34.970 --> 00:33:37.430
And to that end, we wishedyour lordship here:

592
00:33:37.430 --> 00:33:40.500
to avoid the censures ofthe carping world.

593
00:33:40.500 --> 00:33:43.330
Which, since you came toolate of our intent,

594
00:33:43.330 --> 00:33:46.770
yet witness what you hearwe did intend.

595
00:33:48.530 --> 00:33:53.500
So, my good lord mayor,

596
00:33:53.500 --> 00:33:55.300
we bid farewell.

597
00:34:18.730 --> 00:34:21.070
Go after, after, cousinBuckingham!

598
00:34:21.070 --> 00:34:23.630
The mayor towards Guildhallhies him all in post.

599
00:34:24.630 --> 00:34:26.630
There, at your meet'stadvantage of the time,

600
00:34:26.630 --> 00:34:28.830
infer the bastardy ofEdward's children.

601
00:34:28.830 --> 00:34:31.100
Moreover, urge his hatefulluxury

602
00:34:31.100 --> 00:34:33.530
and bestial appetite inchange of lust,

603
00:34:33.530 --> 00:34:36.600
which stretched unto theirservants, daughters, wives,

604
00:34:36.600 --> 00:34:39.270
even where his raging eyeand savage heart

605
00:34:39.270 --> 00:34:42.200
without control lusted tomake a prey.

606
00:34:42.200 --> 00:34:44.530
Nay, for a need, thus farcome near my person.

607
00:34:44.530 --> 00:34:46.830
Tell them when that mymother went of child

608
00:34:46.830 --> 00:34:48.330
of that insatiate Edward,

609
00:34:48.330 --> 00:34:51.830
noble York, my princelyfather, then had wars inFrance

